jdrasil.algorithms.upperbounds

Class GreedyPermutationDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdrasil.algorithms.upperbounds.GreedyPermutationDecomposer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.Callable<TreeDecomposition<T>>, TreeDecomposer<T>

    public class GreedyPermutationDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeDecomposer<T>, java.io.Serializable
    This class implements greedy permutation heuristics to compute a tree-decomposition. The heuristic eliminates the vertex v that minimises some function f(v), ties are broken randomly. See "Bodlaender and Koster: Treewidth computations I. Upper bounds" for an overview of possible functions f.
